# Generated run output (containment finding F5): HISTORICAL DEFENSE-IN-DEPTH ONLY. Primary protection
# is now the plan-time containment guard in cli.py (_resolve_sealed_output_root), which defaults the
# sealed output root to the CorpusStudio application-data dir and refuses any root resolving inside the
# checkout. These anchors remain to swallow any legacy/stray in-checkout write, and are anchored to the
# repo root ONLY so a legitimate tracked artifact (e.g.
# examples/wbg/adapter-seq1536-baseline/adapter_model.safetensors) is never hidden.
/output/
/engine/output/
